race.comment: EDWARDS (8) made it three wins in a row last start when he scored by 2.75 lengths over 1400m at Charleville. Stepping up a level this time but on current form he is good enough to take this out. ONE THING COUNTS (3) missed the placings two runs back then improved last start but found a couple better over 1500m at Rockhampton, beaten 2.25 lengths after being prominent at the turn. Has the class to figure prominently. RUMBLING AWAY (4) is close to breaking through after two consecutive placings, the latest at Gympie over 1600m. Has a formidable record at this journey with three wins and three placings from seven starts and is expected to run well. LIP SIP SUK (2) ran below expectations last time at Charleville over 1625m, finishing fourth and beaten 7 lengths. Blinkers go on and rates among the leading chances.
